# Material Design 3 Rules

## Design Tokens

✅ **MUST:**
- Use MD3 design tokens via Tailwind classes (`bg-primary`, `text-on-primary`)
- Follow MD3 specifications exactly
- Use MD3 elevation classes (`shadow-elevation-1`)
- Use MD3 typography classes (`text-headline-large`)

❌ **NEVER:**
- Use arbitrary color values (`bg-[#6750a4]`)
- Deviate from MD3 specs
- Create custom variants not in MD3 spec

## Component Variants

✅ **MUST:**
- Implement ALL MD3 variants for each component
- Use MD3 naming (e.g., 'filled', 'outlined' NOT 'solid', 'bordered')

❌ **NEVER:**
- Create custom variants not in MD3 spec
- Skip MD3 variants

## Interactions

✅ **MUST:**
- Implement MD3 state layers
- Use MD3 motion tokens (`transition-all duration-short2 ease-standard`)
- Implement ripple effect where specified

❌ **NEVER:**
- Use custom animations not in MD3

## CVA Pattern for Variants

```typescript
// button.variants.ts
import { cva, type VariantProps } from 'class-variance-authority'

export const buttonVariants = cva(
  'base-classes',
  {
    variants: {
      variant: {
        filled: 'bg-primary text-on-primary',
        outlined: 'border-2 border-outline',
        text: 'bg-transparent',
        elevated: 'bg-surface-container-low shadow-elevation-1',
        tonal: 'bg-secondary-container text-on-secondary-container',
      },
      size: {
        small: 'h-10 px-4',
        medium: 'h-12 px-6',
        large: 'h-14 px-8',
      },
    },
    defaultVariants: {
      variant: 'filled',
      size: 'medium',
    },
  }
)

export type ButtonVariants = VariantProps<typeof buttonVariants>
```

## Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)

✅ **MUST:**
- Meet WCAG 2.1 AA minimum (aim for AAA where feasible)
- Ensure 4.5:1 contrast for text, 3:1 for UI components
- Provide accessible labels for all interactive elements
- Support keyboard navigation (Tab, Enter, Space)
- Show visible focus indicators (never remove)
- Let React Aria handle ARIA attributes
- Add `aria-label` for icon-only components
- Use semantic HTML when possible

❌ **NEVER:**
- Skip accessibility attributes
- Rely on color alone for information
- Create keyboard traps
- Add redundant ARIA (React Aria handles it)
